09/05/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The police arrested a 20-year-old football fan on Saturday (May 8th) who seriously injured a police officer during a match a week ago. The policeman lost an eye during riots at the match between the Dinamo (Zagreb) and Hajduk (Split) in Zagreb on May 1st. In all, 15 police officers and six football fans were injured during and after the game. (HRT, Index - 08/05/10)
